{
  "title": "Refactoring Batch Jobs Using FastAPI with Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This explainer demonstrates how to refactor batch jobs using the FastAPI framework in Python 3.12+, emphasizing its capabilities for asynchronous processing and efficient handling of long-running tasks.",
  "key_points": [
    "Utilize FastAPI's built-in support for async processing",
    "Implement background tasks using third-party libraries like FastAPI-Starlette-BackgroundTasks",
    "Leverage Pydantic models for input validation and data serialization",
    "Use Python 3.12+ features such as async context managers, aisyncio.Queue, and aisyncio.Semaphore",
    "Monitor task progress and handle exceptions gracefully"
  ],
  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "```\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI, Depends\nfrom fastapi.starlette.background import BackgroundTasks\napp = FastAPI()\n\nasync def my_batch_job(queue: aisyncio.Queue):\n    # Long-running task implementation\n\n@app.post('/start_job/')\nasync def start_job(bg_tasks: BackgroundTasks = Depends(bg_tasks)):\n    bg_tasks.add_task(my_batch_job, aisyncio.Queue())\n```"
    }
  ],
  "version_notes": [
    "Python 3.12+ is required for access to new async context managers and other features.",
    "FastAPI >=0.68.0 and FastAPI-Starlette-BackgroundTasks are needed for the background tasks implementation."
  ],
  "caveats": [
    "Ensure to handle exceptions appropriately when working with long-running tasks.",
    "Optimize resource usage by limiting the number of concurrent tasks using aisyncio.Semaphore."
  ]
}
